title_with_entities.text: Cinema Motivations: Exploring the Moviegoing Experiences of Quezon City Gen X and Gen Z

message.text:
📣 Calling All Respondents! 📣

Hello, fellow Tams! ✨ We are 4th-year BA Comm Digital Cinema track Students conducting our thesis entitled:

🎬 “Cinema Motivations: Exploring the Moviegoing Experiences of Quezon City Gen X and Gen Z” 🍿

We’re inviting Gen X (1965–1980) and Gen Z (1997–2012) residents of Quezon City who have watched at least one movie in a cinema within the past 12 months to be part of our study. 💙

Your participation will help us better understand the motivations and experiences of moviegoers across generations. 🕒 The survey only takes 8–12 minutes, and all responses will be kept strictly confidential.

👉 Click the link below to answer the survey and share your voice!

https://forms.gle/LxAjd2ug6pxnDDn57

https://forms.gle/LxAjd2ug6pxnDDn57

https://forms.gle/LxAjd2ug6pxnDDn57

Thank you so much for your support! 🙏✨

We are the 4th Year Digital Cinema track Communication Students conducting a study titled “Cinema Motivations: Exploring the Moviegoing Experiences of Quezon City Gen X and Gen Z” This research is conducted online for accessibility and safety....

title_with_entities.text: Cinema Motivations: Exploring the Moviegoing Experiences of Quezon City Gen X and Gen Z

message.text:
📣 Calling All Respondents! 📣

Hello, fellow Tams! ✨ We are 4th-year BA Comm Digital Cinema track Students conducting our thesis entitled:

🎬 “Cinema Motivations: Exploring the Moviegoing Experiences of Quezon City Gen X and Gen Z” 🍿

We’re inviting Gen X (1965–1980) and Gen Z (1997–2012) residents of Quezon City who have watched at least one movie in a cinema within the past 12 months to be part of our study. 💙

Your participation will help us better understand the motivations and experiences of moviegoers across generations. 🕒 The survey only takes 8–12 minutes, and all responses will be kept strictly confidential.

👉 Click the link below to answer the survey and share your voice!

https://forms.gle/LxAjd2ug6pxnDDn57

https://forms.gle/LxAjd2ug6pxnDDn57

https://forms.gle/LxAjd2ug6pxnDDn57

Thank you so much for your support! 🙏✨

message.text:
Handa ka na bang makiisa sa hiwaga ng mga #ADVOlaryoSaSiquijor? 🕯️✨

Ngayong ikawalo hanggang ika-13 ng Setyembre, gaganapin ang pinakahinihintay na pagtawag ng mga bagong mamamahayag. Nais mo bang ialay ang iyong kakayahan? 

Bisitahin ang #IslaDelAdvo sa FEU Plaza upang makiisa sa paglalahad ng katotohanan.

Magrehistro sa online gamit ang mga link na ito: 

FEU Manila: 
https://forms.gle/we4m9zJW1sotS3kw7

FEU Makati:
https://forms.gle/efWus2559v3GaszK9 

Hihintayin namin kayo! #TamHunt2025

Para sa iba pang mga katanungan, maaari kayong makipag-ugnayan kay Jenah Javier sa 0915 092 2160 o magpadala ng email sa feuadvocate.recruitment@gmail.com

taking up space in the society has been constantly stripped off us, youth and students. but it's time to reclaim our spot and battle for the right. what better way to do your social responsibility but not just echo and be the voice of the struggling community!

being a journalist is not bounded by the four walls of the classroom nor the four gates of feu. it is in our biggest capacity to use our medium to go out and serve with the marginalized sectors. may it be through articles, photos, or illustrations, nothing is more important than being socially conscious citizens by being empathetic to our surrounding.

from writing about student struggle to mass struggle, we see how each of us are interconnected with each other which should push us to keep on making noise. ika nga, the pen is mightier than the sword. but it should know what side it should swerve into. nothing is comfortable in a journalist's job, with the state of press freedom, we can only do so much more but to keep on exercising our duties.

while we are being deprived of our rights through bureaucratic and anti-student policies, neoliberal education, and commercialization, we continue to charge with passion to break barriers and move with the community.

feu advocate as the official student publication of feu, with its 91 years of legacy and was shut down by the marcos sr. regime continues to deliver veracious reportage and principled advocacy. be part of this history and continue to write history!!!

join news section daw 🦊 sige ikaw dito!

Handa ka na bang makiisa sa hiwaga ng mga #ADVOlaryoSaSiquijor? 🕯️✨

Ngayong ikawalo hanggang ika-13 ng Setyembre, gaganapin ang pinakahinihintay na pagtawag ng mga bagong mamamahayag. Nais mo bang ialay ang iyong kakayahan? 

Bisitahin ang #IslaDelAdvo sa FEU Plaza upang makiisa sa paglalahad ng katotohanan.

Magrehistro sa online gamit ang mga link na ito: 

FEU Manila: 
https://forms.gle/we4m9zJW1sotS3kw7

FEU Makati:
https://forms.gle/efWus2559v3GaszK9 

Hihintayin namin kayo! #TamHunt2025

Para sa iba pang mga katanungan, maaari kayong makipag-ugnayan kay Jenah Javier sa 0915 092 2160 o magpadala ng email sa feuadvocate.recruitment@gmail.com
